	directAnswerHtml={`<strong style="color: var(--color-ink);">If you are Sikh, the Father's Heart Bible™ is offered to you in deep respect.</strong> You devote your heart to the one God — Waheguru, the formless and eternal Creator who is present in all — and you live out that devotion in honest labor, equality, generosity, and selfless service (seva). These are beautiful and worthy. The <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">Father's Heart Bible™</a> is a fresh English translation you can read and <em>listen to</em> free — and it reveals that same one God as a <em>Father</em>. Whether you searched "does the one God love me personally," "is God a Father," "Bible verses about God's love," or "who is God in the Bible" — the heart of it is this: the one Creator you remember by name longs to be known not only as Lord, but as a near, tender Father who calls you His own child.`}
