	aFatherHeading={`A Father for Sikhs`}
	aFatherBodyHtml={`<p>The Father's Heart Bible™ does not ask you to love a different God. It gently introduces the one God — the formless, eternal Creator you already remember by name — as a <strong style="color: var(--color-ink);">Father</strong> who is near, personal, and tender toward you.</p><p>In Scripture, the one God is holy and over all things, exactly as you honor Him to be. And He is also revealed as a Father who knows each of His children by name, who runs to welcome them home, who delights in them — not because they have earned it through enough merit, but because of His own grace and love. This is not a smaller God; it is the same one God, drawing close.</p><p>So before you are a servant, a worker, a giver — all of which are good — you are invited to be received simply as a beloved child. Your heavenly Father wants to be the near and steady presence beneath your devotion, the one who says: I see you, I know you, and I love you as My own — rest in My grace.</p>`}
