	wordHeading={`His Word will not return void`}
	wordBodyHtml={`<p>You may not feel everything change the first time you read. That is alright. The Father's love is not a fleeting feeling — it is a foundation, and foundations are built quietly, one day at a time. Each verse you take in is the one God planting something gentle and true within you.</p><p class="mt-4" style="color: var(--color-ink);">"My word… will not return to me empty, but will accomplish that which I purpose." <span style="color: var(--color-muted);">— Isaiah 55:11</span></p>`}
	fatherSaysHeading={`What your Father says over you`}
	fatherSaysHtml={`<p>"I know you by name. I have seen your devotion, your honest work, and every quiet act of service you offered without being seen — and I tell you, I am near. I am not only the One you remember from afar; I am your Father, and I love you as My own child.</p><p>You do not have to carry the weight of earning your way to Me. Come, and rest in My grace. What you have longed for — to be personally and tenderly known — you already are, by Me. I delight in you, I call you Mine, and I will never let you go."</p>`}
	prayerHeading={`A prayer for Sikhs`}
	prayerHtml={`<p>Our Father, we thank You for our Sikh friends and neighbors — for their sincere devotion to the one God, for their honest work, their love of equality, and their selfless service to others. These things are beautiful, and they honor You.</p><p>We ask that You would draw near to each one and reveal Yourself not only as the great Creator over all, but as a personal, tender Father. Where there is the weight of merit and striving, let them encounter Your rest. Where there is longing to be truly and personally known, let them discover they are already known and loved by You as Your own beloved child.</p><p>Father, meet them with grace, with gentleness, and with the deep dignity their devotion deserves. Let them hear Your voice as a loving Father speaking their name, and may they come to know the assurance and nearness of belonging to You.</p><p>In Jesus' name, amen.</p>`}
